The 2017 London Marathon champion Kenya's Daniel Wanjiru has been suspended for a doping violation. The Athletes Integrity Unit (AIU) on Tuesday announced having provisionally suspended Wanjiru with immediate effect for an Athlete Biological Passport violation under the World Athletics Anti-Doping Rules. Wanjiru shot to the limelight when he edged out Ethiopian long-distance running legend Kenenisa Bekele to London Marathon victory in 2017 before finishing eighth in the 2017 London World Championships.  